{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-13916/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-13916"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:39:16"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["low key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man watches as a woman eats a piece of food off of her fork."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13916/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-13916","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13916/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-13916"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13916/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13916/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13916/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13916/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13916/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13916/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13916/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13916/canvas/1/3b9848bb-1cab-4cb2-bb08-80701f36aaff","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T14:43:27.439Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The production team used Stanley Kubrick’s <em>Barry Lyndon</em>, whose nighttime scenes were lit entirely by candlelight, as a reference point to shoot and light this scene (Lux Lighting, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW163496186 BCX2\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kpi393XkzUo\"><u>Lighting Phantom Thread</u></a>”). Adam Nayman proposes another Kubrick reference: “Showing up together at a Christmas party gilded around the edges like a Klimt painting, they resemble Tom Cruise and Nicole Kidman at the outset of <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW163496186 BCX2\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YdMlgtvdPJA\"><em><u>Eyes Wide Shut</u></em></a>—a couple perched on the verge of disaster or dissolution” (Nayman, <em>Masterworks</em>, 225).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13916/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:275.84415584415575,134.80519480519473,1348.0519480519483,583.6363636363637"}}}]}]}]}